				Hey Dwyvyrn, <br>  <br> You sure are showing your true colors here.  You seem pretty bitter.  If you were such a great person, I think you would just walk away and let this die.  Instead, you seem very vindictive - posting on our boards, trying to boycott our server... who needs their diapers changed again?  To tell you the truth, I was mildly opposed to the move before, but could have lived with it.  And I was happy when I heard that it was cancelled.  I had no strong feelings one way or the other.  It is since that time, reading your posts, and getting a sense of your attitude that I have developed a strong opinion and feel inclined to post here. <br>  <br> Couple of points to consider:  I wonder what exactly the motivation was to come to Torv over other servers...  Could it be that we are a young server and that you would have free reign over the planes/dragons?  Hmmm... sounds pretty attractive, doesn't it?  Can't blame you.  Of course that's what we want too.  Why not go to a mature server where you could fit in and cause a little less disruption?  A server where you would have less impact.  I don't think you understand the impact you would have on our server. <br>  <br> Here's my story:  I quit my 29 monk on another server 5 minutes after I got the message that Torv came up.  I have played him to 39 since.  The thrill of playing on a new server is unlike any other I have had in EQ up till that point.  I remember the first couple days not wanting to go past the 1st Inn in E Common  because there were only 10 ppl in zone and didn't want to get slaughtered by a lion.  Or standing at the edge of the desert in NRo pulling spiders and beetles, and getting wiped out by madmen because there were no high levels to help out if things got ugly.  Going to Oasis the first time with 12 people in the zone (instead of 70 on my old server).  Or HH barely surviving solo against the Shralok (instead of the FFA on my old server), or aviaks in SK when there weren't enough ppl in the zone to kill the avocets for us (instead of 100+ on my old server).   Get the picture?  This isn't just about overcrowding, there is a real sense of danger as you are doing these things.  Well, unfortunately, I don't have as much time to play as many people, so I have not been able to stay near the front of the pack, yet many of my friends from the beginning have made it to ~50 and they are just now beginning to be able to attempt dragons/planes.  As a matter of fact, we had an attempt at Naggy this weekend this past weekend, and it failed.  Although I am not of level to participate yet, many of my friends were.  And I know that I soon will be.  As it stands, I still have a chance to make it in on the tail end of some of the first dragon/planes raids.  As I explained before, the idea here is that it is immensely more fun doing this stuff (sense of adventure/danger) when the zones aren't camped/packed.  There are no waiting lists for the dragons/planes yet.  Experience on other servers tells us that this will not last long.  It is a special time on a server when these types of events first start happening.  Well guess what?  Add 20 or more ~50+ characters to this picture (who are admittedly experienced and efficient at this stuff), and I am gonna be missing out on alot of this stuff while it is happening for the first times.  We would like to accomplish these things by ourselves, with the same groups of people that have worked together for the past few months to get this far. <br>  <br> Oh yeah, I forgot - you guys are self-proclaimed 'some of the nicest people around' and we would 'be lucky to have you join our community'.  I wonder if you consider yourself one of these people Dwyv?  Your posts to date seem to indicate otherwise. <br>  <br> Also, for those of you who do not make it over to torvonnilous.net, here is an interesting link to the message board of the guild in question.  It will at least give you some insigt into what their motivations were:   <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://pub12.ezboard.com/fcoegeneral.showMessage?topicID=80.topic">http://pub12.ezboard.com/fcoegeneral.showMessage?topicID=80.topic</a>  <br>  <br> Although, I don't doubt that most of you are nice, and are very good players, people like Dwyv completely undermine that image.  Although some people may have been jerks when expressing their view that Torv does not want to have a bunch of high-levels inserted on our server, there are jerks on every server.  That does not change the validity of our view in general as a server.  The point is, this is our server.  It is just starting to come into it's own.  I don't think that not wanting to share that with others outside our family is such a bad thing.  It does not make us bad people.  It does mean that we are proud of what we have done and we are looking forward to moving onwards and upwards without your help. <br>  <br> If you made it this far, I'm surprised frankly :)  I hope that this has shed a little more light on the attitude on our server (although I can only speak for myself, I'm pretty sure I'm close to what the feeling is).  I do wish the best to the people on Test who have *not* been flaming our boards.  The wipes were a rotten thing to do.  I hope that you find an appropriate home on another server. <br> 		

